WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

2
00:00:29.238 --> 00:00:30.572
<i>LA's an immigrant city.</i>

3
00:00:31.532 --> 00:00:33.593
<i>From the Chumash to the Persians</i>

4
00:00:33.617 --> 00:00:35.869
<i>to the Vietnamese
to everyone else in between.</i>

5
00:00:36.620 --> 00:00:37.746
<i>This is where they come.</i>

6
00:00:40.916 --> 00:00:44.646
<i>"A writer once said. "Los Angeles
gives the feeling of the future</i>

7
00:00:44.670 --> 00:00:46.463
<i>more strongly than any city I know of.</i>

8
00:00:47.005 --> 00:00:48.441
<i>"A bad future. too."</i>

9
00:00:48.465 --> 00:00:50.008
Wait for me. right?

10
00:00:50.884 --> 00:00:53.029
-Thought I told you...
-Fuck y'all!

11
00:00:53.053 --> 00:00:55.281
-<i>But. I don't know about that.</i>
-Hey.

12
00:00:55.305 --> 00:00:57.015
<i>I'm an immigrant too. I guess.</i>

13
00:00:57.599 --> 00:00:59.434
<i>I think LA's got a lot of good to it.</i>

14
00:01:01.687 --> 00:01:02.997
There he is.

15
00:01:03.021 --> 00:01:04.022
Let's do this.

16
00:01:07.943 --> 00:01:12.406
<i>I'll admit it though.
It's a hard town. no argument there.</i>

17
00:02:29.399 --> 00:02:34.696
<i>♪ And now the purple dusk
Of twilight time ♪</i>

18
00:02:35.489 --> 00:02:40.452
<i>♪ Steals across the meadows of my heart ♪</i>

19
00:02:42.246 --> 00:02:47.918
<i>♪ High up in the sky
The little stars climb ♪</i>

20
00:02:48.502 --> 00:02:53.465
<i>♪ Always reminding me that we're apart ♪</i>

21
00:02:56.802 --> 00:03:01.640
<i>♪ You wander down the lane
And far away ♪</i>

22
00:03:02.391 --> 00:03:03.392
Sweet pool.

23
00:03:07.813 --> 00:03:10.458
Hey. So what did your car guy say?

24
00:03:10.482 --> 00:03:13.670
Listen. most times.
a whip like that rolls in…

25
00:03:13.694 --> 00:03:17.215
…the mechanic makes a sad face. takes
whatever it really costs and adds a zero.

26
00:03:18.365 --> 00:03:20.385
But. Sugar. today you are in luck.

27
00:03:20.409 --> 00:03:21.493
'cause my guy Billy…

28
00:03:22.536 --> 00:03:24.180
I mean. he's like an honest Gandalf.

29
00:03:24.204 --> 00:03:25.723
I thought you were going
for an oil change.

30
00:03:25.747 --> 00:03:29.227
You can't leave a car like that
up on blocks for six months

31
00:03:29.251 --> 00:03:31.646
and expect her to be up and running
with just an oil change.

32
00:03:31.670 --> 00:03:33.430
All right? But she's good now.
She's perfect.

33
00:03:36.758 --> 00:03:38.069
All right.

34
00:03:42.389 --> 00:03:43.390
There she goes.

35
00:03:48.562 --> 00:03:50.957
-So you stay here. huh?
-Live here.

36
00:03:50.981 --> 00:03:53.233
You live here?

37
00:03:55.652 --> 00:03:56.737
You must charge a lot.

38
00:03:57.613 --> 00:03:59.323
Industry rates. from what I'm told.

39
00:04:00.699 --> 00:04:01.992
Nice industry.

40
00:04:02.910 --> 00:04:03.911
It ain't bad.

41
00:04:11.168 --> 00:04:13.212
Hey. You want a job. Val?

42
00:04:14.254 --> 00:04:17.317
I gotta be somewhere in a couple hours.
but… …sure. What do you got?

43
00:04:17.341 --> 00:04:18.884
No. no. no. A job. Like a job-job.

44
00:04:20.511 --> 00:04:21.678
Working with me.

45
00:04:22.221 --> 00:04:24.556
You know?
Ongoing position.

46
00:04:27.100 --> 00:04:30.604
No. I'm serious. I mean. we just met. but
you're disciplined. you're resourceful.

47
00:04:31.146 --> 00:04:32.624
And to be honest with you. I could…

48
00:04:32.648 --> 00:04:35.275
I could. uh…
I could do with the help.

49
00:04:38.737 --> 00:04:39.738
Right.

50
00:04:40.781 --> 00:04:43.009
No.
but I don't wanna presume.

51
00:04:43.033 --> 00:04:44.743
Not if you. uh…

52
00:04:45.536 --> 00:04:46.930
Um… No. I mean I'm…

53
00:04:46.954 --> 00:04:50.499
I'm always on the lookout for. uh.
new shit. new job opportunities.

54
00:04:51.416 --> 00:04:53.085
-So you'll think about it?
-For sure.

55
00:04:53.877 --> 00:04:55.522
Yeah. cool. Let… Let me think on it.

56
00:04:55.546 --> 00:04:56.755
Good. Think about it.

57
00:04:57.381 --> 00:05:00.133
-Good.
-Good.

58
00:05:00.968 --> 00:05:01.969
Okay.

59
00:05:19.361 --> 00:05:21.905
Danny! Throw your hands up.
Danny. Come on.

60
00:05:23.657 --> 00:05:24.717
Move your feet.

61
00:05:26.994 --> 00:05:28.304
That's it. Move.

62
00:05:31.123 --> 00:05:32.457
<i>Here we go.</i>

63
00:05:33.750 --> 00:05:34.960
That's it. Come on.

64
00:05:37.462 --> 00:05:39.131
Move your feet. Move your feet.

65
00:05:46.972 --> 00:05:48.765
<i>They call it the Sweet Science.</i>

66
00:05:49.349 --> 00:05:51.786
<i>It's brutal. but they call it sport.</i>

67
00:05:51.810 --> 00:05:53.478
Danny.

68
00:05:55.272 --> 00:05:56.273
Danny!

69
00:05:56.815 --> 00:05:58.418
<i>I gotta admit.</i>

70
00:05:58.442 --> 00:06:01.337
<i>whatever you wanna call it.
it's hard to look away.</i>

71
00:06:01.361 --> 00:06:03.280
He's stealing drugs
from the fucking hospital?

72
00:06:04.031 --> 00:06:05.490
It's the last place he was seen.

73
00:06:06.366 --> 00:06:09.179
Jesus. He-He's not always like this.

74
00:06:09.203 --> 00:06:11.723
-I mean. these days he is. but…
-You don't need to explain.

75
00:06:11.747 --> 00:06:14.416
I'm not explaining anything.
I'm just telling it like it is.

76
00:06:15.501 --> 00:06:16.502
Of course.

77
00:06:18.879 --> 00:06:21.798
And the. uh…
the police aren't looking for him?

78
00:06:22.508 --> 00:06:23.675
As far as I know.

79
00:06:25.260 --> 00:06:26.321
-Excuse me.
-Remember.

80
00:06:26.345 --> 00:06:28.156
when you're in there.
keep your feet moving.

81
00:06:28.180 --> 00:06:29.515
Hey. Tom. What do you got?

82
00:06:30.474 --> 00:06:32.785
Hands up. guts up. Keep your hands up.

83
00:06:32.809 --> 00:06:34.078
What's up. Coach?

84
00:06:34.102 --> 00:06:35.562
-Agent?
-I wish.

85
00:06:36.271 --> 00:06:37.999
No. just some guy helping with Ji.

86
00:06:38.023 --> 00:06:41.586
-Ah. Ji. Your crazy brother Ji. huh?
-Yeah.

87
00:06:41.610 --> 00:06:43.463
Listen. good job the other night.

88
00:06:43.487 --> 00:06:47.550
Eddie Mbanefo…
…is two classes above you.

89
00:06:47.574 --> 00:06:50.678
Now. he moves like a cement pig.
but he's no tomato can.

90
00:06:50.702 --> 00:06:52.454
Thanks. Teddy.

91
00:06:53.163 --> 00:06:54.224
That guy was slow.

92
00:06:54.248 --> 00:06:56.017
Just had to work
his middle and stop his feet

93
00:06:56.041 --> 00:06:57.936
and then. pop. pop. come up high.

94
00:06:57.960 --> 00:07:00.438
Big things are coming for you. Danny.

95
00:07:00.462 --> 00:07:02.232
-Stay focused.
-Okay.

96
00:07:02.256 --> 00:07:04.192
-All right. I'll text when I'm there.
-All right.

97
00:07:04.216 --> 00:07:06.218
Okay. bye.

98
00:07:07.386 --> 00:07:08.780
-Sorry.
-So we're good. right?

99
00:07:08.804 --> 00:07:11.866
You'll just. uh…
…you know. keep me updated?

100
00:07:11.890 --> 00:07:15.829
Definitely. yeah. I gotta go.
Thank you for letting me come by.

101
00:07:15.853 --> 00:07:16.913
Sure.

102
00:07:16.937 --> 00:07:19.606
Yo. that… that call. Was it about Ji?

103
00:07:21.400 --> 00:07:23.086
I'll… I'll let you know.

104
00:07:23.110 --> 00:07:24.111
Okay.

105
00:07:32.578 --> 00:07:34.204
<i>Everything comes to an end.</i>

106
00:07:36.290 --> 00:07:38.083
<i>Sooner than you think sometimes.</i>

107
00:07:41.128 --> 00:07:44.882
<i>From the side suns of Andromeda.
to the detamorphs on Paloma.</i>

108
00:07:47.801 --> 00:07:48.886
<i>Everything dies.</i>

109
00:07:53.098 --> 00:07:54.099
<i>But still…</i>

110
00:07:57.144 --> 00:07:59.229
<i>I'm hoping I don't find Ji here.</i>

111
00:08:05.235 --> 00:08:06.737
They're bringing him.

112
00:08:10.616 --> 00:08:12.510
-<i>Tom Flybjerg.</i>
-Oh. fucking…

113
00:08:12.534 --> 00:08:15.597
<i>I helped him a few years ago
when his wife went missing hiking in Ojai.</i>

114
00:08:15.621 --> 00:08:17.682
Say. you know how
to put stuff on Instagram?

115
00:08:17.706 --> 00:08:20.000
<i>Turned out.
she'd only gone missing from Tom.</i>

116
00:08:21.919 --> 00:08:23.646
Hey. Flybjerg. coming in.

117
00:08:23.670 --> 00:08:24.671
Here we go.

118
00:08:28.675 --> 00:08:30.511
Early 20s Asian male.

119
00:08:36.642 --> 00:08:37.643
Good resemblance.

120
00:08:39.061 --> 00:08:40.871
All right. Good news.

121
00:08:40.895 --> 00:08:41.938
Mmm. not for him.

122
00:08:43.106 --> 00:08:45.585
You said it was a gang hit?
He doesn't look like a banger.

123
00:08:45.609 --> 00:08:48.695
He's probably a civilian.
Wrong place. wrong time kind of thing.

124
00:08:49.655 --> 00:08:51.341
-That his stuff?
-Yeah.

125
00:08:51.365 --> 00:08:54.886
Wallet. photos. a few bills. a phone card.
But no photo ID.

126
00:08:54.910 --> 00:08:55.970
-Can I?
-Yeah.

127
00:09:03.335 --> 00:09:07.172
He's an immigrant. Recent.
He's probably still waiting on his papers.

128
00:09:07.840 --> 00:09:10.693
Trace the activity on this phone card
and you can find his parents.

129
00:09:10.717 --> 00:09:12.970
It'll just be one number
he called over and over.

130
00:09:13.595 --> 00:09:14.656
Fair.

131
00:09:14.680 --> 00:09:15.949
On a brighter note.

132
00:09:15.973 --> 00:09:18.785
in the "arc of history bends
towards justice" category.

133
00:09:18.809 --> 00:09:19.994
Katie. where's the shooter?

134
00:09:20.018 --> 00:09:21.019
Over here.

135
00:09:22.312 --> 00:09:24.231
It's like fucking Mardi Gras in here.

136
00:09:25.357 --> 00:09:27.901
LAPD ran up on him two blocks away.

137
00:09:35.659 --> 00:09:36.761
"Ez4"?

138
00:09:36.785 --> 00:09:39.204
Gang tat probably. I'll ask around.

139
00:09:42.249 --> 00:09:44.352
A gang member
killing a civilian?

140
00:09:44.376 --> 00:09:46.003
Mmm. it happens.

141
00:09:46.795 --> 00:09:49.464
Um. initiation.
get your wings sort of thing.

142
00:09:50.299 --> 00:09:53.260
Or he's just an idiot. shot the wrong guy.

143
00:09:59.224 --> 00:10:00.577
You mind?

144
00:10:00.601 --> 00:10:01.602
Go ahead.

145
00:10:10.527 --> 00:10:14.990
Sometimes it still works
if he's just… dead.

146
00:10:17.409 --> 00:10:18.911
Don't ask how we learned that.

147
00:10:24.583 --> 00:10:26.186
I think you were right.

148
00:10:26.210 --> 00:10:27.437
About what?

149
00:10:27.461 --> 00:10:28.670
They shot the wrong guy.

150
00:10:30.005 --> 00:10:33.318
<i>I guess I was still hoping whatever
trouble Ji had gotten himself into</i>

151
00:10:33.342 --> 00:10:35.093
<i>was of the self-inflicted variety.</i>

152
00:10:36.011 --> 00:10:38.114
<i>But someone really is after him.</i>

153
00:10:38.138 --> 00:10:39.181
<i>Someone serious.</i>

154
00:10:42.768 --> 00:10:43.936
<i>He's right to be afraid.</i>

155
00:10:45.395 --> 00:10:48.649
<i>Still. it gave me a thought
on where to look next.</i>

156
00:10:49.816 --> 00:10:50.984
<i>Or where to look again.</i>

157
00:10:56.406 --> 00:10:57.741
-Oh!
-Damn it!

158
00:11:00.702 --> 00:11:02.138
Hey.

159
00:11:02.162 --> 00:11:03.348
You okay?

160
00:11:03.372 --> 00:11:06.959
I'm fine. I just got fired.
so. kinda having a bad day.

161
00:11:07.876 --> 00:11:09.586
Aw. I'm sorry. That's… uh. that's too bad.

162
00:11:10.337 --> 00:11:12.047
-I got you.
-Uh. thanks. uh…

163
00:11:12.589 --> 00:11:13.789
Thank you.

164
00:11:14.967 --> 00:11:17.177
-Thank you. Yeah.
-Yeah. All right.

165
00:11:19.263 --> 00:11:20.657
Hey. Good luck.

166
00:11:20.681 --> 00:11:21.682
Thanks.

167
00:11:29.857 --> 00:11:31.084
Blaine.

168
00:11:31.108 --> 00:11:35.296
"If it's December 1941 in Casablanca.
what time is it in New York?"

169
00:11:37.364 --> 00:11:39.384
"My watch stopped."

170
00:11:39.408 --> 00:11:40.468
-You saw the film?
-Yes!

171
00:11:40.492 --> 00:11:42.220
-What'd you think?
-Phenomenal.

172
00:11:42.244 --> 00:11:43.245
Good.

173
00:11:44.037 --> 00:11:45.747
I have a favor to ask.

174
00:11:52.754 --> 00:11:53.755
That's him.

175
00:11:54.840 --> 00:11:56.067
-Ah.
-Uh-huh.

176
00:11:56.091 --> 00:11:57.443
-That's your guy?
-Yeah.

177
00:11:57.467 --> 00:11:58.987
Leaving the fourth floor.

178
00:11:59.011 --> 00:12:00.530
You have cameras in the stairwell?

179
00:12:00.554 --> 00:12:01.614
No.

180
00:12:01.638 --> 00:12:04.075
All right. can you show me the. uh…
the exit the stairs lead to?

181
00:12:04.099 --> 00:12:05.100
Okay.

182
00:12:14.067 --> 00:12:15.068
Mm-mmm.

183
00:12:16.069 --> 00:12:17.237
Where'd he go?

184
00:12:17.988 --> 00:12:22.326
I mean it's been nine. ten minutes.
and he's still…

185
00:12:22.951 --> 00:12:24.679
Oh. there he is.

186
00:12:28.373 --> 00:12:30.459
Why'd it take him so long
to get down the stairs?

187
00:12:31.001 --> 00:12:32.753
He must've gone to another floor.

188
00:12:34.880 --> 00:12:36.590
-Check the cameras?
-Yeah.

189
00:12:38.175 --> 00:12:39.510
You're right. Here he is.

190
00:12:41.428 --> 00:12:43.722
Exiting the fifth-floor stairwell.

191
00:12:47.893 --> 00:12:49.662
Here he is a few minutes later.

192
00:12:49.686 --> 00:12:51.772
Whoa. whoa. stop. Go back.

193
00:12:52.397 --> 00:12:54.900
Okay. go forward. slowly.
Slow. slow. slow. stop.

194
00:12:57.444 --> 00:12:58.654
Whoa.

195
00:13:00.447 --> 00:13:01.758
Something spooked him.

196
00:13:01.782 --> 00:13:02.783
Yeah.

197
00:13:05.869 --> 00:13:09.849
He doesn't show up
at the elevator or the nurse's station.

198
00:13:09.873 --> 00:13:15.629
so wherever he went for those few minutes
have to be off that hallway.

199
00:13:16.255 --> 00:13:17.695
<i>A hallway on the fifth floor.</i>

200
00:13:40.195 --> 00:13:43.657
<i>"Jesus Alejandro Jaquez. 22 years old.</i>

201
00:13:44.741 --> 00:13:46.553
<i>Admitted April 27th."</i>

202
00:13:46.577 --> 00:13:48.161
Three days before Ji was here.

203
00:13:49.079 --> 00:13:51.224
"Patient arrived
with multiple gunshot wounds."

204
00:13:51.248 --> 00:13:54.811
Multiple transfusions.
Intubation due to perforated lung.

205
00:13:54.835 --> 00:13:56.545
<i>"Emergency splenectomy."</i>

206
00:14:05.679 --> 00:14:06.680
Poor kid.

207
00:14:07.514 --> 00:14:08.515
He didn't make it.

208
00:14:13.812 --> 00:14:15.314
<i>What were you doing. Ji?</i>

209
00:14:42.758 --> 00:14:44.718
<i>How does a dead man take a picture?</i>

210
00:14:48.680 --> 00:14:49.681
<i>Unless…</i>

211
00:14:51.225 --> 00:14:52.434
<i>Someone else was there.</i>

212
00:14:54.895 --> 00:14:56.873
All right. Now we're looking
for someone else.

213
00:14:56.897 --> 00:14:59.083
Visitor. fifth floor. same time as my guy.

214
00:14:59.107 --> 00:15:03.171
It was late.
so nurses. orderlies…

215
00:15:14.915 --> 00:15:16.166
Him.

216
00:15:21.380 --> 00:15:22.381
Hmm.

217
00:15:24.049 --> 00:15:26.176
He's hiding his face
from the cameras.

218
00:15:28.804 --> 00:15:29.888
Who is he?

219
00:15:45.028 --> 00:15:46.029
<i>Who is that?</i>

220
00:16:19.938 --> 00:16:21.624
Ji-Ho! There he is!

221
00:16:21.648 --> 00:16:22.834
Hey. guys.

222
00:16:22.858 --> 00:16:24.377
Rocky too!

223
00:16:24.401 --> 00:16:25.461
Hey. Lucy.

224
00:16:25.485 --> 00:16:26.671
Hi. Danny.

225
00:16:26.695 --> 00:16:29.007
Hungry?
I have some Sundubu Jjigae left over.

226
00:16:29.031 --> 00:16:30.383
I'm all right. thank you.

227
00:16:30.407 --> 00:16:32.302
Just wanted to say good night.

228
00:16:32.326 --> 00:16:33.327
Goodnight.

229
00:16:33.994 --> 00:16:35.194
By the way.

230
00:16:35.996 --> 00:16:37.289
And so rent?

231
00:16:38.332 --> 00:16:39.333
Is coming soon?

232
00:16:40.125 --> 00:16:41.925
You haven't received our rent. yet?

233
00:16:42.961 --> 00:16:45.273
Ji-Seok didn't pay you?

234
00:16:45.297 --> 00:16:47.275
Are you fucking serious. Ji?

235
00:16:47.299 --> 00:16:50.093
Where the hell are you?
Call me back right fucking now!

236
00:16:51.303 --> 00:16:52.679
Son of a bitch! Fuck!

237
00:16:56.016 --> 00:16:58.810
<i>It's not easy
being on your own sometimes.</i>

238
00:16:59.978 --> 00:17:01.873
<i>Before. there were thousands of us.</i>

239
00:17:01.897 --> 00:17:06.335
<i>I could always come home
and find someone to talk to. Now?</i>

240
00:17:06.359 --> 00:17:07.879
<i>You have no new messages.</i>

241
00:17:07.903 --> 00:17:09.946
<i>Well. now I have work to do.</i>

242
00:17:11.740 --> 00:17:13.951
<i>Who are these people after Ji?</i>

243
00:17:16.286 --> 00:17:18.680
<i>LA's got street gangs.
Everyone knows that.</i>

244
00:17:18.704 --> 00:17:20.975
<i>From 18th street to Glendale.</i>

245
00:17:20.999 --> 00:17:22.751
<i>From Long Beach up into Ventura.</i>

246
00:17:24.044 --> 00:17:27.881
<i>Drugs and guns and senseless drive-bys
is what we're told on the news.</i>

247
00:17:29.091 --> 00:17:30.676
<i>But that's not the whole story.</i>

248
00:17:31.718 --> 00:17:34.555
<i>Right or wrong. gangs are like families.</i>

249
00:17:35.222 --> 00:17:37.116
<i>And families make you feel
part of something.</i>

250
00:17:37.140 --> 00:17:39.393
<i>And that's a powerful thing.</i>

251
00:17:41.311 --> 00:17:44.606
<i>Like I said. it's hard being on your own.</i>

252
00:18:11.884 --> 00:18:13.093
Hello again.

253
00:18:16.138 --> 00:18:17.139
Hello.

254
00:18:20.642 --> 00:18:22.996
-Made up your mind?
-Just the usual. please. Eric.

255
00:18:23.020 --> 00:18:25.039
Mung beans with ghee
and a side of papaya.

256
00:18:25.063 --> 00:18:27.584
And I wanted to ask. Um…

257
00:18:27.608 --> 00:18:29.234
How did the callback go?

258
00:18:30.068 --> 00:18:31.254
I didn't get it.

259
00:18:31.278 --> 00:18:32.380
No!

260
00:18:32.404 --> 00:18:34.716
-Aw. I know you wanted that one.
-I know.

261
00:18:34.740 --> 00:18:36.217
I thought I had it too.

262
00:18:36.241 --> 00:18:38.887
That sucks. I remember Sydney Greenstreet.

263
00:18:38.911 --> 00:18:41.222
he didn't get his big break
until <i>The Maltese Falcon.</i>

264
00:18:41.246 --> 00:18:42.706
when he was what. 61?

265
00:18:43.665 --> 00:18:45.501
Never know what's gonna
happen next. you know?

266
00:18:50.005 --> 00:18:51.381
That was nice of you.

267
00:18:52.966 --> 00:18:54.051
What? What was?

268
00:18:55.552 --> 00:18:58.096
What you said.
I bet you turned his whole night around.

269
00:19:03.268 --> 00:19:05.521
Men don't usually like being called nice.

270
00:19:06.355 --> 00:19:08.917
Not all men. Not only men. but…

271
00:19:08.941 --> 00:19:11.860
…they think
it's a sign of weakness.

272
00:19:12.528 --> 00:19:13.862
Only. I think it's the opposite.

273
00:19:14.446 --> 00:19:16.073
It's a powerful quality.

274
00:19:16.657 --> 00:19:18.367
This world could use a lot more of it.

275
00:19:20.452 --> 00:19:21.995
At least that's my experience.

276
00:19:25.374 --> 00:19:27.814
-How was everything tonight?
-Thank you. Delicious.

277
00:20:14.006 --> 00:20:15.465
You're nice too.

278
00:20:21.930 --> 00:20:22.931
You're not nice?

279
00:20:25.350 --> 00:20:28.270
I don't think it's the first thing
people would say about me.

280
00:20:31.815 --> 00:20:34.735
What would they say?

281
00:20:36.486 --> 00:20:41.843
Um… hardworking. passionate. humanitarian.

282
00:20:41.867 --> 00:20:42.927
Wow.

283
00:20:42.951 --> 00:20:44.721
Oh. my God. I sound so boring.

284
00:20:44.745 --> 00:20:46.598
No. you don't.

285
00:20:46.622 --> 00:20:48.123
Okay. let me try again.

286
00:20:48.957 --> 00:20:50.834
Uh… they would say…

287
00:20:51.710 --> 00:20:55.047
She enjoys talking
to nice men in restaurants.

288
00:21:02.846 --> 00:21:04.365
I'm sorry. I have to take this.

289
00:21:04.389 --> 00:21:05.390
Of course.

290
00:21:06.308 --> 00:21:07.684
To be continued.

291
00:21:12.773 --> 00:21:13.857
That was weird.

292
00:21:15.776 --> 00:21:16.777
Mm-mmm.

293
00:21:17.903 --> 00:21:19.130
No. no. no.

294
00:21:19.154 --> 00:21:20.781
That's… That's not allowed.

295
00:21:28.705 --> 00:21:29.706
Fuck.

296
00:21:42.511 --> 00:21:44.847
<i>Yo. yo. yo!
So what's up. champ? You in or what?</i>

297
00:21:45.347 --> 00:21:46.348
Uh…

298
00:21:46.974 --> 00:21:48.701
Is there room for me on the next one?

299
00:21:48.725 --> 00:21:51.120
<i>Yeah. baby! We actually
got a gig tomorrow night.</i>

300
00:21:51.144 --> 00:21:53.957
<i>You wanna make that cheddar?
I'll come pick you up.</i>

301
00:21:53.981 --> 00:21:56.084
-All right. I'm down.
<i>-Sick.</i>

302
00:21:56.108 --> 00:21:57.526
<i>I'll see you on the flip. bitch.</i>

303
00:22:37.649 --> 00:22:39.484
<i>Good morning. Senator Pavich.</i>

304
00:22:46.700 --> 00:22:49.036
<i>Former senator. I should say.</i>

305
00:22:51.038 --> 00:22:53.874
<i>He's now the CEO
of a brand new tech company.</i>

306
00:22:55.250 --> 00:22:56.710
<i>They put out a press release</i>

307
00:22:57.211 --> 00:23:01.048
<i>dedicated to developing brand new
solutions to age-old problems.</i>

308
00:23:04.176 --> 00:23:07.012
<i>So. he's either working on
a cure for cancer or…</i>

309
00:23:09.097 --> 00:23:10.098
<i>Or what?</i>

310
00:23:32.913 --> 00:23:34.039
Nice meeting you.

311
00:23:34.540 --> 00:23:36.041
<i>Whatever it is.</i>

312
00:23:36.625 --> 00:23:37.960
<i>it looks like he's hiring.</i>

313
00:23:41.380 --> 00:23:42.774
Huh.

314
00:23:42.798 --> 00:23:44.216
<i>I should probably go.</i>

315
00:23:45.092 --> 00:23:46.468
<i>Clock's ticking on Ji Moon.</i>

316
00:23:52.224 --> 00:23:55.036
<i>You've reached Danny Moon.
Leave a message.</i>

317
00:23:55.060 --> 00:23:56.246
Danny. it's Sugar.

318
00:23:56.270 --> 00:23:58.510
I've been trying to reach you.
Call me when you get this.

319
00:23:59.439 --> 00:24:02.860
<i>Figured my best lead was to try and learn
something about Jesus Jaquez.</i>

320
00:24:03.443 --> 00:24:05.779
<i>the kid who died
in that hospital room with Ji.</i>

321
00:24:06.655 --> 00:24:09.032
<i>I got a next of kin address from Hannah.</i>

322
00:25:01.835 --> 00:25:02.836
Mrs. Jaquez.

323
00:25:03.253 --> 00:25:04.314
Yes?

324
00:25:04.338 --> 00:25:06.232
My condolences about Jesus.

325
00:25:06.256 --> 00:25:07.466
My name is John.

326
00:25:08.258 --> 00:25:11.053
May I come in
and ask a few questions about him?

327
00:25:12.346 --> 00:25:13.555
Only take a moment?

328
00:25:15.265 --> 00:25:17.434
Come in.

329
00:25:27.069 --> 00:25:28.362
<i>Poor woman.</i>

330
00:25:28.862 --> 00:25:31.240
<i>Grief. I'm familiar.</i>

331
00:25:32.324 --> 00:25:35.702
<i>When I first lost my sister.
I could barely move.</i>

332
00:25:51.134 --> 00:25:52.135
<i>Señora.</i>

333
00:25:52.970 --> 00:25:56.056
Would it be possible to see Jesus' room?

334
00:25:57.015 --> 00:25:58.016
Thank you.

335
00:26:17.035 --> 00:26:18.412
<i>Aztec art.</i>

336
00:26:23.667 --> 00:26:24.877
<i>He had interests.</i>

337
00:26:29.464 --> 00:26:30.465
<i>A home.</i>

338
00:26:34.887 --> 00:26:36.013
<i>He was loved.</i>

339
00:26:52.863 --> 00:26:54.966
I'm sorry to bother you
any more than I have.

340
00:26:54.990 --> 00:26:58.785
but I'm hoping to spare someone else
from the pain you're suffering.

341
00:26:59.745 --> 00:27:00.746
I'm listening.

342
00:27:01.747 --> 00:27:02.748
Thank you.

343
00:27:07.377 --> 00:27:08.670
You recognize this person?

344
00:27:09.129 --> 00:27:11.465
Did you ever see him with Jesus?

345
00:27:16.803 --> 00:27:17.804
What about him?

346
00:27:30.484 --> 00:27:31.961
The picture

347
00:27:31.985 --> 00:27:33.087
in the bedroom.

348
00:27:33.111 --> 00:27:34.172
The woman?

349
00:27:34.196 --> 00:27:36.031
Sandra.

350
00:27:37.115 --> 00:27:38.116
His mom.

351
00:27:39.034 --> 00:27:40.094
Your daughter?

352
00:27:40.118 --> 00:27:41.370
Yes.

353
00:27:42.120 --> 00:27:43.181
Where is she?

354
00:27:43.205 --> 00:27:44.265
Streets.

355
00:27:44.289 --> 00:27:45.749
Drugs.

356
00:27:46.166 --> 00:27:47.209
Crazy.

357
00:27:50.212 --> 00:27:52.548
Was Jesus still in touch with her at all?

358
00:27:53.048 --> 00:27:54.859
Yes. they were best friends.

359
00:27:54.883 --> 00:27:56.218
Confidants.

360
00:27:58.011 --> 00:28:00.222
She called him "Chuy."

361
00:28:00.681 --> 00:28:02.266
"Chuy?"

362
00:28:18.115 --> 00:28:20.117
Can I do something for you?

363
00:28:21.743 --> 00:28:23.203
Like what?

364
00:29:29.186 --> 00:29:30.187
Hey.

365
00:29:34.107 --> 00:29:35.108
Hey.

366
00:29:37.319 --> 00:29:40.507
I'd like you to make a phone call
to your boss. like you did before.

367
00:29:41.907 --> 00:29:43.551
I ain't got no boss. G.

368
00:29:43.575 --> 00:29:45.678
I'm a CEO with a pension plan.

369
00:29:45.702 --> 00:29:47.496
Uh-huh. You seen this?

370
00:29:51.792 --> 00:29:52.936
You have.

371
00:29:52.960 --> 00:29:54.211
You take this photo?

372
00:29:59.216 --> 00:30:00.217
Nah. you didn't.

373
00:30:00.843 --> 00:30:03.696
All right. So what I'm asking
is that you tell your boss

374
00:30:03.720 --> 00:30:05.472
I wanna talk to the person who did.

375
00:30:07.182 --> 00:30:08.183
Here.

376
00:30:08.809 --> 00:30:10.227
Take it. I'm not the police.

377
00:30:10.894 --> 00:30:13.540
I heard there's been a misunderstanding.
I just want to clear it up.

378
00:30:15.232 --> 00:30:16.233
Okay.

379
00:30:17.401 --> 00:30:18.610
Let's clear it up then.

380
00:30:21.446 --> 00:30:24.616
Meantime. G? You probably wanna
get right the fuck out of here.

381
00:31:14.208 --> 00:31:15.768
Hey. I've been calling you.

382
00:31:15.792 --> 00:31:17.711
Oh. my bad. man.
I've been… I've been busy.

383
00:31:18.921 --> 00:31:20.589
I got a lead I wanna ask you about.

384
00:31:21.173 --> 00:31:22.484
Sure. uh. but I got work.

385
00:31:22.508 --> 00:31:24.360
A friend's about to pick me up
in a sec. so…

386
00:31:24.384 --> 00:31:25.761
Okay. I'll make it quick.

387
00:31:29.223 --> 00:31:33.661
You ever heard Ji mention the Ez4s?

388
00:31:33.685 --> 00:31:35.854
-The what?
-Ez4s. LA street gang.

389
00:31:36.480 --> 00:31:38.565
Yeah. your brother's on their radar
for some reason.

390
00:31:39.191 --> 00:31:41.693
A street gang? Are you fucking serious?

391
00:31:42.653 --> 00:31:45.465
I don't know what his involvement is yet.
He may not have done anything wrong...

392
00:31:45.489 --> 00:31:47.574
You told me he ripped drugs
off a hospital. right?

393
00:31:48.700 --> 00:31:50.053
-He did.
-What are you talking about

394
00:31:50.077 --> 00:31:53.163
he didn't do anything wrong? Ji's been
doing shit wrong for fucking years.

395
00:31:54.456 --> 00:31:56.250
Sorry.

396
00:32:00.754 --> 00:32:01.755
Fuck.

397
00:32:07.135 --> 00:32:08.136
You all right?

398
00:32:12.474 --> 00:32:14.309
Something else you want to tell me about?

399
00:32:17.312 --> 00:32:21.275
What are you. a fucking shrink now?
I haven't even paid you for the PI part.

400
00:32:21.984 --> 00:32:23.711
Uh. don't worry about the money.

401
00:32:23.735 --> 00:32:26.965
Yeah. well. you're rich.
so you can say that.

402
00:32:26.989 --> 00:32:27.990
That's not why.

403
00:32:28.866 --> 00:32:29.867
No?

404
00:32:31.743 --> 00:32:34.264
How many of those expensive-ass suits
do you own?

405
00:32:34.288 --> 00:32:35.289
How many exactly?

406
00:32:36.456 --> 00:32:37.499
Uh… I don't know.

407
00:32:38.792 --> 00:32:40.210
'Cause you're rich. bro.

408
00:32:41.086 --> 00:32:43.406
Look. my friend's about to be here.
Thanks for checking in.

409
00:32:48.844 --> 00:32:50.554
Listen. Danny. Whatever's happening…

410
00:32:52.097 --> 00:32:53.974
Whatever it is that's going on. just…

411
00:32:55.559 --> 00:32:56.560
let me help you.

412
00:32:58.687 --> 00:32:59.688
No.

413
00:33:07.696 --> 00:33:09.156
Fucking Ji.

414
00:33:12.618 --> 00:33:15.013
Hey. there he is.

415
00:33:15.037 --> 00:33:16.330
Welcome back. champ.

416
00:33:34.932 --> 00:33:36.016
Okay. coming up.

417
00:33:45.734 --> 00:33:47.653
All right. bitches. Let's get to work.

418
00:33:54.034 --> 00:33:56.888
Yo. yo. yo. come on. chill!
Chill. bro! What the fuck?

419
00:33:57.996 --> 00:33:59.933
-Get the fuck back.
-What are y'all doing. man?

420
00:34:01.416 --> 00:34:03.728
Get the fuck off me. man! Fuck!

421
00:34:06.129 --> 00:34:07.190
Yo. chill!

422
00:34:11.051 --> 00:34:12.553
Let's go. let's go. let's go.

423
00:34:13.887 --> 00:34:15.013
Ay. yo. let's go.

424
00:34:15.681 --> 00:34:16.723
Let's go. come on.

425
00:34:17.224 --> 00:34:19.117
Get all that in the truck. Let's go.

426
00:34:30.112 --> 00:34:31.905
Yo. where did that guard come from?

427
00:34:32.406 --> 00:34:35.468
I didn't see him. and then he was…
He was right up on me.

428
00:34:35.492 --> 00:34:38.387
It's all right. man. chill.
You handled the fuck out of him.

429
00:34:38.411 --> 00:34:39.722
Fuck.

430
00:35:02.769 --> 00:35:03.770
Hey.

431
00:35:05.189 --> 00:35:06.190
Thank you.

432
00:35:11.486 --> 00:35:12.487
Um…

433
00:35:15.490 --> 00:35:17.534
So. I stole some bathrobes from the pool.

434
00:35:19.411 --> 00:35:21.163
I just took a bunch of them.
Piled them up.

435
00:35:22.289 --> 00:35:24.833
Walked right through.
I mean. no one said shit.

436
00:35:25.417 --> 00:35:26.752
I'm gonna sell them on eBay.

437
00:35:29.213 --> 00:35:30.273
Cool.

438
00:35:30.297 --> 00:35:31.423
Okay.

439
00:35:34.009 --> 00:35:35.135
What's going on here?

440
00:35:37.721 --> 00:35:40.557
Uh. sometimes I make mistakes.
but most of the time.

441
00:35:41.725 --> 00:35:43.435
I see people real well.

442
00:35:47.523 --> 00:35:48.565
You see people.

443
00:35:53.779 --> 00:35:55.030
What do you see in me?

444
00:35:55.531 --> 00:35:56.883
More than a thief.

445
00:35:59.409 --> 00:36:02.013
Yeah. You got that right.

446
00:36:02.037 --> 00:36:03.306
And I need a partner.

447
00:36:04.706 --> 00:36:07.769
In private investigation.
I don't even know what's…

448
00:36:07.793 --> 00:36:09.127
I'll tea… I'll teach you.

449
00:36:09.628 --> 00:36:12.440
All right. you got a camera?
Not a phone camera. An actual camera.

450
00:36:12.464 --> 00:36:14.317
No. I know what you mean.
Yeah. I can find one.

451
00:36:14.341 --> 00:36:15.884
Mm-hmm. You got a car?

452
00:36:16.552 --> 00:36:18.428
-Mm-hmm.
-A not-stolen one?

453
00:36:18.929 --> 00:36:20.323
Sure.

454
00:36:20.347 --> 00:36:21.348
All right.

455
00:36:27.980 --> 00:36:29.356
Does that figure look okay?

456
00:36:35.028 --> 00:36:36.673
-Yeah?
-Mm-hmm. Per week?

457
00:36:36.697 --> 00:36:37.990
Mm-hmm.

458
00:36:39.575 --> 00:36:42.619
Okay. You start tomorrow.

459
00:36:44.079 --> 00:36:45.414
I've done some things.

460
00:36:47.958 --> 00:36:50.043
More than bathrobes and cars.

461
00:36:50.794 --> 00:36:52.129
I've done some things too.

462
00:36:56.592 --> 00:36:57.593
All right.

463
00:36:58.635 --> 00:36:59.678
Let's fucking go.

464
00:37:00.554 --> 00:37:01.680
-Okay.
-All right.

465
00:37:02.973 --> 00:37:04.057
Mmm.

466
00:37:06.018 --> 00:37:07.394
Caesar salad and New York strip.

467
00:37:08.228 --> 00:37:09.646
I put it on your room.

468
00:37:44.348 --> 00:37:46.683
<i>You have no new messages.</i>

469
00:38:00.864 --> 00:38:01.925
Sugar.

470
00:38:01.949 --> 00:38:04.743
<i>I heard you want to talk
to the man who took that photo.</i>

471
00:38:05.869 --> 00:38:06.870
Yeah.

472
00:38:07.538 --> 00:38:09.039
<i>Grab a pen. Here's an address.</i>

473
00:38:12.626 --> 00:38:13.627
Go ahead.

474
00:38:18.090 --> 00:38:20.384
<i>I have a bad feeling
about this case.</i>

475
00:38:20.926 --> 00:38:23.470
<i>Says the hero in every PI movie ever made.</i>

476
00:38:27.599 --> 00:38:29.226
<i>And he's usually right to worry.</i>

477
00:38:30.936 --> 00:38:34.147
<i>It only goes from bad to worse
from that point on.</i>

478
00:38:35.816 --> 00:38:36.817
<i>But he keeps going.</i>

479
00:38:37.860 --> 00:38:38.861
<i>He doesn't stop.</i>

480
00:38:39.611 --> 00:38:41.154
<i>Not on a case like this.</i>

481
00:38:43.365 --> 00:38:44.366
<i>He can't.</i>

482
00:38:45.325 --> 00:38:47.452
<i>He's a PI. And the PI has to know.</i>

483
00:38:51.540 --> 00:38:52.791
<i>And so he'll keep going…</i>

484
00:38:55.502 --> 00:38:56.879
<i>And going…</i>

485
00:39:04.845 --> 00:39:06.471
<i>Right up until the very end.</i>

486
00:40:20.504 --> 00:40:22.482
<i>♪ And now the purple dusk
Of twilight time ♪</i>

487
00:40:26.552 --> 00:40:30.722
<i>♪ Steals across the meadows of my heart ♪</i>

488
00:40:33.392 --> 00:40:38.480
<i>♪ High up in the sky
The little stars climb ♪</i>

489
00:40:39.523 --> 00:40:46.113
<i>♪ Always reminding me that we're apart ♪</i>

490
00:40:47.823 --> 00:40:52.286
<i>♪ You wandered down the lane
And far away ♪</i>

491
00:40:54.663 --> 00:40:59.751
<i>♪ Leaving me a song that will not die ♪</i>

492
00:41:03.046 --> 00:41:09.052
<i>♪ Love is now the stardust of yesterday ♪</i>

493
00:41:10.721 --> 00:41:17.561
<i>♪ The music of the years gone by ♪</i>

494
00:41:20.230 --> 00:41:24.651
<i>♪ Sometimes I wonder ♪</i>

495
00:41:25.652 --> 00:41:27.905
<i>♪ Why I spend ♪</i>

496
00:41:28.822 --> 00:41:32.618
<i>♪ The lonely night ♪</i>

497
00:41:33.285 --> 00:41:35.996
<i>♪ Dreaming of a song ♪</i>

497
